3 § 1843. VERMONT HOSPITAL SECURITY PLAN
4 (a)(1) The Agency of Human Services or designee shall administer the
5 Vermont Hospital Security Plan to provide Vermont residents with access to
6 and coverage for health care services received in a hospital and for payments to
7 hospitals for health care services provided.
8 (2) Vermonters who are eligible for or are enrolled in a publicly funded
9 health care program shall be eligible for coverage of any benefits provided by
10 the Vermont Hospital Security Plan that are not covered by the publicly funded
11 health care program. As used in this subdivision, “publicly funded health care
12 program” means Medicare, Medicaid, Dr. Dynasaur, VPharm, another
13 Medicaid-waiver program, or any other program providing health benefits that
14 is funded in whole or in part with federal funds.
15 (b) The Vermont Hospital Security Plan shall:
16 (1) provide each hospital in this State with a negotiated annual payment
17 based on the budget of the individual hospital for health care services provided
18 by that hospital to all patients, including patients who are not Vermont
19 residents;
20 (2) provide for the collection of payments for health care services
21 provided by hospitals in this State to patients who are not Vermont residents,
