5 § 1846. VERMONT HOSPITAL SECURITY TRUST FUND
6 (a) The Vermont Hospital Security Trust Fund is established as a special
7 fund for the purpose of financing health care services provided by hospitals to
8 beneficiaries of the Vermont Hospital Security Plan.
9 (b) Into the Fund shall be deposited:
10 (1) transfers from the General Fund authorized by the General
11 Assembly;
12 (2) proceeds from grants, donations, contributions, taxes, and any other
13 sources of revenue as may be provided by statute or rule;
14 (3) transfers of all federal receipts related to health care services
15 provided by hospitals, including all Medicaid receipts and, upon federal
16 approval, all Medicare receipts; and
17 (4) revenue for the sources established to fund the Vermont Hospital
18 Security Plan established in this subchapter.
19 (c) The Secretary shall administer the Fund in accordance with 32 V.S.A.
20 chapter 7, subchapter 5, except that all interest earned on Fund balances shall
