2 COMMITTEE; FUNDING MECHANISMS; REPORT
3 (a) There is created the Vermont Hospital Security Plan Special Committee
4 to recommend to the General Assembly appropriate funding mechanisms for
5 the Vermont Hospital Security Plan.
6 (b) The Special Committee shall be composed of the following members:
7 (1) two members of the House of Representatives, one from the House
8 Committee on Health Care and one from the House Committee on Ways and
9 Means, appointed by the Speaker of the House;
10 (2) two members of the Senate, one from the Senate Committee on
11 Health and Welfare and one from the Senate Committee on Finance, appointed
12 by the President Pro Tempore;
13 (3) the Secretary of Human Services or designee;
14 (4) the Chair of the Green Mountain Care Board or designee; and
15 (5) the Commissioner of Taxes or designee.
16 (c) Powers and duties. The Special Committee shall consider how to fund
17 the Vermont Hospital Security Plan with and without federal waivers to secure
18 the participation of Medicaid and Medicare, including at least the following
19 funding sources:
20 (1) an income tax;
21 (2) a payroll tax;
